{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Phase-1 debug triage (rebar-debug batch): NOT a code defect - working-as-designed per ADR 0043. The [operator-attested] criterion kind deliberately requires a human to record out-of-band evidence, and certification propagates upward by design, so an agent-executed epic with such a child legitimately cannot self-sign. No cited contract says it should. Escalating as a design change (e.g. a certified_pending_operator_attestation tri-state), not an auto-fix."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784486495264970001,"uuid":"ae4ff72b-8982-4b9f-ae8c-ee4ba87da425"}